<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-06-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-06-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="636" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d636">
                    <head>No. 636.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Thompson</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Port au Prince
                                    Hayti</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-06-19"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 19, 1888</date>.
                            (Received June 26.)</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 189.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to inform you of the arrival of the
                        French man-of-war <hi rend="italic">Du Couëdic</hi> on the 9th and her
                        departure on the 13th instant. The French ship of war <hi rend="italic">Bison</hi> is expected.</p>
                    <p>H. M. S. <hi rend="italic">Ready</hi> arrived here the 13th, relieving the
                            <hi rend="italic">Wrangler</hi>, the latter returning to Jamaica.</p>
                    <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                    <closer><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">John E. W.
                                Thompson.</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>